Whoa. Cool.

14:33.006 --> 14:35.640
(Russian accent)
Deputy Director Bullock.

14:35.642 --> 14:39.177
You screw with my arms dealing
for the last time.

14:39.179 --> 14:41.045
Oh, this is great.
Heh!

14:41.047 --> 14:43.147
I was kind of freaking out with
the bag over my head

14:43.149 --> 14:44.482
and all the Russian talk.

14:44.484 --> 14:46.317
You know, which always sounds
angry.

14:46.319 --> 14:47.752
(making garbled noises)

14:47.754 --> 14:49.053
(chuckles)
But -- Whew! --

14:49.055 --> 14:50.321
you got the wrong guy.
Heh.

14:50.323 --> 14:52.056
You are Bullock.

14:52.058 --> 14:55.693
You win deejay battle every
night and run C.I.A. every day.

14:55.695 --> 14:58.096
You say so on Facebook page.

14:58.098 --> 14:59.898
That's not me. Tonight's
the first time

14:59.900 --> 15:02.734
I won the deejay thing.
I'm just a normal guy.

15:02.736 --> 15:04.569
Let me show you.
Mm...okay.

15:04.571 --> 15:08.006
But don't close that window.
I am picking movie seats.

15:08.008 --> 15:09.941
Look. I'm a piano tuner.

15:09.943 --> 15:11.242
My name's Jim Steele.

15:11.244 --> 15:12.610
Morons!

15:12.612 --> 15:14.579
I have no time for this!

15:14.581 --> 15:18.049
Is my daughter Tasha's birthday.
Sorry for inconvenience.

15:18.051 --> 15:19.617
I understand.
I have a daughter.

15:19.619 --> 15:21.185
Throw him from cliff.

15:21.187 --> 15:23.721
(screaming)

15:23.723 --> 15:26.291
(screaming continues)

15:27.761 --> 15:30.228
Oh, my God. For a second,
I thought that was me.

15:30.230 --> 15:31.963
(crying)

15:31.965 --> 15:34.465
The deejay
is ruining my party!

15:34.467 --> 15:36.467
Don't cry, cookie.

15:36.469 --> 15:38.636
Throw deejay from cliff
after this guy.

15:38.638 --> 15:42.540
Wait. I'm a great deejay.
I can save her party.

15:47.147 --> 15:51.115
Save Tasha's party and you can
forget about cliff.

15:51.117 --> 15:53.551
Forget about your beautiful
cliff?

15:53.553 --> 15:55.987
Not on your life.
It's majestic!

15:55.989 --> 15:57.588
You make joke.

15:57.590 --> 16:00.425
But two favorite things are
daughter and cliff.

16:00.427 --> 16:04.996
Oh! Who do you think is my
favorite character on "Cheers"?

16:04.998 --> 16:06.397
Cliff?

16:06.399 --> 16:08.433
No. Norm.

16:08.435 --> 16:11.936
He always have pleasure of
being with Cliff.

16:11.938 --> 16:14.339
(laughs)

16:14.341 --> 16:16.407
(laughter)

16:16.409 --> 16:18.076
(screaming)

16:18.078 --> 16:20.912
(thuds)
My memory stick!

16:20.914 --> 16:22.146
Is problem?

16:22.148 --> 16:23.815
Uh, no.
No, n-no problem.

16:23.817 --> 16:26.417
I just need
a new memory stick.

16:26.419 --> 16:28.286
They're only magnets.
Metal.

16:28.288 --> 16:30.688
Stuff you mine.
Like from this cliff!

16:30.690 --> 16:33.424
Careful, guy.
That is my cliff.

16:33.426 --> 16:35.159
(grunts)
(gasps)

16:35.161 --> 16:37.929
There's got to be
something here.

16:37.931 --> 16:41.499
Iron ore.

16:41.501 --> 16:43.334
Nickel-cadmium.

16:43.336 --> 16:47.138
The two main ingredients in
a thumb drive.

16:47.140 --> 16:50.675
Full of music.
(kisses)

16:50.677 --> 16:53.277
(dance music plays)

16:59.219 --> 17:02.620
(retching)

17:06.526 --> 17:08.226
Wha-- what's going on?

17:08.228 --> 17:10.728
How did I get back here?
You never left.

17:10.730 --> 17:13.031
You've been on a psychedelic
trip for 24 hours.

17:13.033 --> 17:16.067
But you were never alone.
I saw to that, bro.

17:16.069 --> 17:19.704
Dad, we only have 20 minutes to
get you to the deejay battle.

17:19.706 --> 17:22.306
So, I-I didn't beat Bullock?

17:22.308 --> 17:24.809
No, Stan. You were just humming
the "Cheers" theme song

17:24.811 --> 17:26.544
and shitting yourself.

17:28.014 --> 17:30.581
(tapping)
Testing, testing.

17:30.583 --> 17:32.650
Can't he just play it, Roger?

17:32.652 --> 17:34.652
It's my shift to watch
Stan again.

17:34.654 --> 17:36.220
Look, Stan's as good as dead.

17:36.222 --> 17:38.589
His heart stopped four times
last night, right?

17:38.591 --> 17:40.391
And he's leaving on a suicide
mission tomorrow.

17:40.393 --> 17:43.061
So please, let's focus on
what still matters.

17:43.063 --> 17:46.898
This is the first recording,
at least on Earth, of the turin.

17:46.900 --> 17:49.400
What -- what -- what's this
about a suicide mission?

17:49.402 --> 17:51.269
I thought Dad had
food poisoning.

17:51.271 --> 17:52.870
Look, everybody's gonna be
fine, all right?

17:52.872 --> 17:54.806
Let's just sit and enjoy
the music.

17:58.445 --> 18:01.112
No.
No, it's not the time.

18:01.114 --> 18:03.214
What?! Of course it's the time!
Play it!

18:03.216 --> 18:05.516
You can't just play the turin.

18:05.518 --> 18:07.685
It tells<i> you</i> when to play it.

18:07.687 --> 18:09.887
What in the ffff-- fine!

18:09.889 --> 18:12.123
And is it telling you
anything now?

18:12.125 --> 18:13.758
No.

18:13.760 --> 18:15.393
Is this bullshit, man?

18:15.395 --> 18:17.862
'Cause my best friend is dying
just down the hall.

18:17.864 --> 18:20.531
What is happening?!

18:20.533 --> 18:22.733
(tires screech, horns honk)

18:22.735 --> 18:25.236
It's amazing, but that tea
actually taught me

18:25.238 --> 18:27.205
how to improvise.
Not really.

18:27.207 --> 18:29.774
Taught you how to put someone
else's set on a memory stick.

18:29.776 --> 18:32.110
But if it beats Bullock
and keeps you alive,

18:32.112 --> 18:33.478
that's all that matters.

18:33.480 --> 18:34.912
Listen to you.

18:34.914 --> 18:37.048
Finally coming around
and seeing the value

18:37.050 --> 18:39.083
of a good,
well-thought-out --

18:39.085 --> 18:42.086
(horn blaring)

18:42.088 --> 18:43.321
(steam hissing)

18:43.323 --> 18:45.756
-No! Your music!
-Hayley?

18:45.758 --> 18:47.725
Smith, you idiot!

18:47.727 --> 18:48.993
I had the red.

18:48.995 --> 18:51.662
(tires squealing)

18:51.664 --> 18:53.564
I can't back up.
I'm stuck.

18:53.566 --> 18:56.234
I -- Euuuugh!

18:56.236 --> 18:59.003
HAYLEY: Go with the flow.
Go with the flow.

18:59.005 --> 19:00.471
Go with the flow.
Go with the flow.

19:00.473 --> 19:02.006
Go with the flow.

